From 063a3e0710798faf80b0aeb684ebbce4c0ed7fd4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Enrique Parodi Spalazzi <enrique.parodi@airbus.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 00:18:17 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 04/10] feat[core/lang]: add query::guideAt() for
 cursor-position hints

Grammar-only guidance for tools that want an inline ghost hint next to
the cursor ("a class name", "\`FROM\`", "a comparison operator, \`AND\`,
\`OR\`, \`BETWEEN\`, \`IN\`, or \`NOT\`", ...) without consulting the
type registry. Returns a GuidanceShape enum plus a default
human-readable hint; editors that localize can ignore the string and
derive their own from the shape.

The positional FSM that drove complete() is extracted into a private
fsm.h/fsm.cpp so complete and guideAt share the same walk rather than
drifting apart.

Two small hint-text fixups bundled in:
- Drop the "expected " prefix from guidance strings. They are labels,
  not complaints.
- Drop the optional \`.\` from the classPathTail hint. Completion
  delivers fully qualified class names in one shot, so the user never
  needs to type the inter-segment dot manually.
